{
  "video_id": "RWiI7AkDX-o",
  "title": "An underwater art museum, teeming with life | Jason deCaires Taylor",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13142.0,
      "end_time": 14293.0,
      "text": "Ten years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14318.0,
      "end_time": 16213.0,
      "text": "I had my first exhibition here."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16638.0,
      "end_time": 20654.0,
      "text": "I had no idea if it would work or was at all possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20678.0,
      "end_time": 24910.0,
      "text": "but with a few small steps and a very steep learning curve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24115.0,
      "end_time": 27357.0,
      "text": "I made my first sculpture, called \"The Lost Correspondent.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28406.0,
      "end_time": 31823.0,
      "text": "Teaming up with a marine biologist and a local dive center,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31847.0,
      "end_time": 34516.0,
      "text": "I submerged the work off the coast of Grenada,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34540.0,
      "end_time": 37195.0,
      "text": "in an area decimated by Hurricane Ivan."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37957.0,
      "end_time": 40830.0,
      "text": "And then this incredible thing happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40554.0,
      "end_time": 41923.0,
      "text": "It transformed."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43675.0,
      "end_time": 45455.0,
      "text": "One sculpture became two."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46955.0,
      "end_time": 49154.0,
      "text": "Two quickly became 26."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 50756.0,
      "end_time": 51907.0,
      "text": "And before I knew it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51931.0,
      "end_time": 54772.0,
      "text": "we had the world&#39;s first underwater sculpture park."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56730.0,
      "end_time": 61577.0,
      "text": "In 2009, I moved to Mexico and started by casting local fisherman."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 62950.0,
      "end_time": 64790.0,
      "text": "This grew to a small community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 66218.0,
      "end_time": 69886.0,
      "text": "to almost an entire movement of people in defense of the sea."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 71228.0,
      "end_time": 73920.0,
      "text": "And then finally, to an underwater museum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 73945.0,
      "end_time": 75997.0,
      "text": "with over 500 living sculptures."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 78760.0,
      "end_time": 80934.0,
      "text": "Gardening, it seems, is not just for greenhouses."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 83375.0,
      "end_time": 86170.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve since scaled up the designs:"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 86410.0,
      "end_time": 90151.0,
      "text": "\"Ocean Atlas,\" in the Bahamas, rising 16 feet up to the surface"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 90175.0,
      "end_time": 91896.0,
      "text": "and weighing over 40 tons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 93825.0,
      "end_time": 95613.0,
      "text": "to now currently in Lanzarote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 95637.0,
      "end_time": 98772.0,
      "text": "where I&#39;m making an underwater botanical garden,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 98796.0,
      "end_time": 101102.0,
      "text": "the first of its kind in the Atlantic Ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 102834.0,
      "end_time": 107840.0,
      "text": "Each project, we use materials and designs that help encourage life;"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 107108.0,
      "end_time": 112905.0,
      "text": "a long-lasting pH-neutral cement provides a stable and permanent platform."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 113398.0,
      "end_time": 116262.0,
      "text": "It is textured to allow coral polyps to attach."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 117262.0,
      "end_time": 119979.0,
      "text": "We position them down current from natural reefs"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 120300.0,
      "end_time": 123445.0,
      "text": "so that after spawning, there&#39;s areas for them to settle."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 125937.0,
      "end_time": 128835.0,
      "text": "The formations are all configured so that they aggregate fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 128859.00000000001,
      "end_time": 130516.00000000001,
      "text": "on a really large scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 132918.0,
      "end_time": 136479.0,
      "text": "Even this VW Beetle has an internal living habitat"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 136503.0,
      "end_time": 140464.0,
      "text": "to encourage crustaceans such as lobsters and sea urchins."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 142733.0,
      "end_time": 145473.0,
      "text": "So why exhibit my work in the ocean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 145497.0,
      "end_time": 148350.0,
      "text": "Because honestly, it&#39;s really not easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 148590.0,
      "end_time": 151264.0,
      "text": "When you&#39;re in the middle of the sea under a hundred-foot crane,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 151288.0,
      "end_time": 154383.0,
      "text": "trying to lower eight tons down to the sea floor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 154407.0,
      "end_time": 158336.0,
      "text": "you start to wonder whether I shouldn&#39;t have taken up watercolor painting instead."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 158360.0,
      "end_time": 159361.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 159385.0,
      "end_time": 162970.0,
      "text": "But in the end, the results always blow my mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 162122.0,
      "end_time": 166102.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 184791.0,
      "end_time": 187710.0,
      "text": "The ocean is the most incredible exhibition space"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 187735.0,
      "end_time": 189406.0,
      "text": "an artist could ever wish for."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 189430.0,
      "end_time": 192783.0,
      "text": "You have amazing lighting effects changing by the hour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 192807.0,
      "end_time": 197124.0,
      "text": "explosions of sand covering the sculptures in a cloud of mystery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 197148.0,
      "end_time": 199520.0,
      "text": "a unique timeless quality"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 199760.0,
      "end_time": 201116.0,
      "text": "and the procession of inquisitive visitors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 201140.0,
      "end_time": 203873.0,
      "text": "each lending their own special touch to the site."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 203897.0,
      "end_time": 208165.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 231288.0,
      "end_time": 232439.0,
      "text": "But over the years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 232463.0,
      "end_time": 235822.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve realized that the greatest thing about what we do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 235846.0,
      "end_time": 238345.0,
      "text": "the really humbling thing about the work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 238369.0,
      "end_time": 240582.0,
      "text": "is that as soon as we submerge the sculptures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 240606.0,
      "end_time": 242132.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re not ours anymore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 242156.0,
      "end_time": 243704.0,
      "text": "because as soon as we sink them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 243728.0,
      "end_time": 245989.0,
      "text": "the sculptures, they belong to the sea."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 246130.0,
      "end_time": 250320.0,
      "text": "As new reefs form, a new world literally starts to evolve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 250560.0,
      "end_time": 252257.0,
      "text": "a world that continuously amazes me."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 252750.0,
      "end_time": 255218.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a bit of a clich√©, but nothing man-made"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 255242.0,
      "end_time": 257733.0,
      "text": "can ever match the imagination of nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 258591.0,
      "end_time": 261511.0,
      "text": "Sponges look like veins across the faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 262478.0,
      "end_time": 265303.0,
      "text": "Staghorn coral morphs the form."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 266567.0,
      "end_time": 269977.0,
      "text": "Fireworms scrawl white lines as they feed."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 271557.0,
      "end_time": 274731.0,
      "text": "Tunicates explode from the faces."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 276597.0,
      "end_time": 280800.0,
      "text": "Sea urchins crawl across the bodies feeding at night."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 282752.0,
      "end_time": 285941.0,
      "text": "Coralline algae applies a kind of purple paint."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 287671.0,
      "end_time": 291284.0,
      "text": "The deepest red I&#39;ve ever seen in my life lives underwater."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 294235.0,
      "end_time": 296951.0,
      "text": "Gorgonian fans oscillate with the waves."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 299200.0,
      "end_time": 301719.0,
      "text": "Purple sponges breathe water like air."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 303221.0,
      "end_time": 306527.0,
      "text": "And grey angelfish glide silently overhead."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 308832.0,
      "end_time": 311193.0,
      "text": "And the amazing response we&#39;ve had to these works"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 311217.0,
      "end_time": 315370.0,
      "text": "tells me that we&#39;ve managed to plug into something really primal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 315394.0,
      "end_time": 319219.0,
      "text": "because it seems that these images translate across the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 319243.0,
      "end_time": 323840.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s made me focus on my responsibility as an artist"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 323108.0,
      "end_time": 325242.0,
      "text": "and about what I&#39;m trying to achieve."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 325917.0,
      "end_time": 329539.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m standing here today on this boat in the middle of the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 329563.0,
      "end_time": 331286.0,
      "text": "and this couldn&#39;t be a better place"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 331310.0,
      "end_time": 335437.0,
      "text": "to talk about the really, really important effect of my work."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 335461.0,
      "end_time": 337121.0,
      "text": "Because as we all know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 337145.0,
      "end_time": 340191.0,
      "text": "our reefs are dying, and our oceans are in trouble."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 341160.0,
      "end_time": 342430.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s the thing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 342454.0,
      "end_time": 345217.0,
      "text": "the most used, searched and shared image"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 345241.0,
      "end_time": 348121.0,
      "text": "of all my work thus far is this."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 349256.0,
      "end_time": 351405.0,
      "text": "And I think this is for a reason,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 351430.0,
      "end_time": 352949.0,
      "text": "or at least I hope it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 353560.0,
      "end_time": 356700.0,
      "text": "What I really hope is that people are beginning to understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 356724.0,
      "end_time": 360392.0,
      "text": "that when we think of the environment and the destruction of nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 360416.0,
      "end_time": 363282.0,
      "text": "that we need to start thinking about our oceans, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 363684.0,
      "end_time": 366215.0,
      "text": "Since building these sites, we&#39;ve seen some phenomenal"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 366239.0,
      "end_time": 367813.0,
      "text": "and unexpected results."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 368260.0,
      "end_time": 373409.0,
      "text": "Besides creating over 800 square meters of new habitats and living reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 373433.0,
      "end_time": 377457.0,
      "text": "visitors to the marine park in Cancun now divide half their time"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 377481.0,
      "end_time": 380130.0,
      "text": "between the museum and the natural reefs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 380370.0,
      "end_time": 384100.0,
      "text": "providing significant rest for natural, overstressed areas."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 384859.0,
      "end_time": 388726.0,
      "text": "Visitors to \"Ocean Atlas\" in the Bahamas highlighted a leak"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 388750.0,
      "end_time": 390559.0,
      "text": "from a nearby oil refinery."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 391251.0,
      "end_time": 394575.0,
      "text": "The subsequent international media forced the local government"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 394600.0,
      "end_time": 397449.0,
      "text": "to pledge 10 million dollars in coastal cleanups."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 398154.0,
      "end_time": 400528.0,
      "text": "The sculpture park in Grenada was instrumental"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 400552.0,
      "end_time": 404819.0,
      "text": "in the government designating a spot -- a marine-protected area."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 404843.0,
      "end_time": 408202.0,
      "text": "Entrance fees to the park now help fund park rangers"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 408226.0,
      "end_time": 410812.0,
      "text": "to manage tourism and fishing quotas."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 411293.0,
      "end_time": 413901.0,
      "text": "The site was actually listed as a \"Wonder of the World\""
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 413925.0,
      "end_time": 415164.0,
      "text": "by National Geographic."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 416297.0,
      "end_time": 418877.0,
      "text": "So why are we all here today in this room?"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 418901.0,
      "end_time": 420902.0,
      "text": "What do we all have in common?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 421560.0,
      "end_time": 423195.0,
      "text": "I think we all share a fear"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 423219.0,
      "end_time": 425353.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t protect our oceans enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 425837.0,
      "end_time": 427484.0,
      "text": "And one way of thinking about this"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 427508.0,
      "end_time": 430853.0,
      "text": "is that we don&#39;t regard our oceans as sacred,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 430877.0,
      "end_time": 432115.0,
      "text": "and we should."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 432572.0,
      "end_time": 434135.0,
      "text": "When we see incredible places --"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 434159.0,
      "end_time": 438970.0,
      "text": "like the Himalayas or the La Sagrada Fam√≠lia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 438121.0,
      "end_time": 439782.0,
      "text": "or the Mona Lisa, even --"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 439806.0,
      "end_time": 442695.0,
      "text": "when we see these incredible places and things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 442719.0,
      "end_time": 444764.0,
      "text": "we understand their importance."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 444788.0,
      "end_time": 446178.0,
      "text": "We call them sacred,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 446202.0,
      "end_time": 449859.0,
      "text": "and we do our best to cherish them, to protect them"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 449883.0,
      "end_time": 451477.0,
      "text": "and to keep them safe."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 451970.0,
      "end_time": 453185.0,
      "text": "But in order to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 453209.0,
      "end_time": 456539.0,
      "text": "we are the ones that have to assign that value;"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 456563.0,
      "end_time": 458960.0,
      "text": "otherwise, it will be desecrated"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 458120.0,
      "end_time": 460744.0,
      "text": "by someone who doesn&#39;t understand that value."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 461549.0,
      "end_time": 465383.0,
      "text": "So I want to finish up tonight by talking about sacred things."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 465408.0,
      "end_time": 467562.0,
      "text": "When we were naming the site in Cancun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 467586.0,
      "end_time": 471904.0,
      "text": "we named it a museum for a very important and simple reason:"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 471928.0,
      "end_time": 474355.0,
      "text": "museums are places of preservation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 474379.0,
      "end_time": 477173.0,
      "text": "of conservation and of education."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 477524.0,
      "end_time": 480960.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re places where we keep objects of great value to us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 480984.0,
      "end_time": 484920.0,
      "text": "where we simply treasure them for them being themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 484966.0,
      "end_time": 487753.0,
      "text": "If someone was to throw an egg at the Sistine Chapel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 487777.0,
      "end_time": 489306.0,
      "text": "we&#39;d all go crazy."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 489704.0,
      "end_time": 492170.0,
      "text": "If someone wanted to build a seven-star hotel"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 492194.0,
      "end_time": 494900.0,
      "text": "at the bottom of the Grand Canyon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 494330.0,
      "end_time": 496161.0,
      "text": "then we would laugh them out of Arizona."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 496494.0,
      "end_time": 500903.0,
      "text": "Yet every day we dredge, pollute and overfish our oceans."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 500927.0,
      "end_time": 503333.0,
      "text": "And I think it&#39;s easier for us to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 503357.0,
      "end_time": 505453.0,
      "text": "because when we see the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 505477.0,
      "end_time": 507405.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t see the havoc we&#39;re wreaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 507429.0,
      "end_time": 508998.0,
      "text": "Because for most people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 509230.0,
      "end_time": 510523.0,
      "text": "the ocean is like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 510980.0,
      "end_time": 512131.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s really hard"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 512155.0,
      "end_time": 517573.0,
      "text": "to think of something that&#39;s just so plain and so enormous, as fragile."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 517597.0,
      "end_time": 520949.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s simply too massive, too vast, too endless."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 521385.99999999994,
      "end_time": 522608.99999999994,
      "text": "And what do you see here?"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 522634.0,
      "end_time": 525323.0,
      "text": "I think most people actually look past to the horizon."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 525713.0,
      "end_time": 527401.0,
      "text": "So I think there&#39;s a real danger"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 527426.0,
      "end_time": 530313.0,
      "text": "that we never really see the sea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 530337.0,
      "end_time": 531846.0,
      "text": "and if we don&#39;t really see it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 531870.0,
      "end_time": 534269.0,
      "text": "if it doesn&#39;t have its own iconography,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 534293.0,
      "end_time": 536305.0,
      "text": "if we miss its majesty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 536329.0,
      "end_time": 539327.0,
      "text": "then there&#39;s a big danger that we take it for granted."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 540772.0,
      "end_time": 544890.0,
      "text": "Cancun is famous for spring break,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 544113.0,
      "end_time": 546372.0,
      "text": "tequila and foam parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 546396.0,
      "end_time": 549939.0,
      "text": "And its waters are where frat boys can ride around on Jet Skis"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 549963.0,
      "end_time": 551224.0,
      "text": "and banana boats."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 551590.0,
      "end_time": 555603.0,
      "text": "But because of our work there, there&#39;s now a little corner of Cancun"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 555627.0,
      "end_time": 558309.0,
      "text": "that is simply precious for being itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 559710.0,
      "end_time": 561702.0,
      "text": "And we don&#39;t want to stop in Grenada,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 561726.0,
      "end_time": 564360.0,
      "text": "in Cancun or the Bahamas."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 564496.0,
      "end_time": 568387.0,
      "text": "Just last month, I installed these Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 568411.0,
      "end_time": 569911.0,
      "text": "in the Thames River,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 571620.0,
      "end_time": 574564.0,
      "text": "in central London, right in front of the Houses of Parliament,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 574588.0,
      "end_time": 577545.0,
      "text": "putting a stark message about climate change"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 577569.0,
      "end_time": 581392.0,
      "text": "in front of the people that have the power to help change things."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 583490.0,
      "end_time": 586870.0,
      "text": "Because for me, this is just the beginning of the mission."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 586111.0,
      "end_time": 588617.0,
      "text": "We want to team up with other inventors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 588641.0,
      "end_time": 592562.0,
      "text": "creators, philanthropists, educators, biologists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 592586.0,
      "end_time": 594960.0,
      "text": "to see better futures for our oceans."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 594984.0,
      "end_time": 597532.0,
      "text": "And we want to see beyond sculpture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 597556.0,
      "end_time": 598964.0,
      "text": "beyond art, even."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 599995.0,
      "end_time": 602413.0,
      "text": "Say you&#39;re a 14-year-old kid from the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 602437.0,
      "end_time": 604159.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;ve never seen the ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 604476.0,
      "end_time": 608690.0,
      "text": "And instead of getting taken to the natural history museum"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 608930.0,
      "end_time": 609680.0,
      "text": "or an aquarium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 609705.0,
      "end_time": 612227.0,
      "text": "you get taken out to the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 612251.0,
      "end_time": 615120.0,
      "text": "to an underwater Noah&#39;s Ark,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 615360.0,
      "end_time": 619600.0,
      "text": "which you can access through a dry-glass viewing tunnel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 619300.0,
      "end_time": 621432.0,
      "text": "where you can see all the wildlife of the land"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 621456.0,
      "end_time": 623805.0,
      "text": "be colonized by the wildlife of the ocean."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 624290.0,
      "end_time": 626216.0,
      "text": "Clearly, it would blow your mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 627290.0,
      "end_time": 630251.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s think big and let&#39;s think deep."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 630569.0,
      "end_time": 634500.0,
      "text": "Who knows where our imagination and willpower can lead us?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 634290.0,
      "end_time": 636977.0,
      "text": "I hope that by bringing our art into the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 637100.0,
      "end_time": 640530.0,
      "text": "that not only do we take advantage of amazing creativity"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 640554.0,
      "end_time": 642689.0,
      "text": "and visual impact of the setting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 642713.0,
      "end_time": 645159.0,
      "text": "but that we are also giving something back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 645183.0,
      "end_time": 648540.0,
      "text": "and by encouraging new environments to thrive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 648565.0,
      "end_time": 653634.0,
      "text": "and in some way opening up a new -- or maybe it&#39;s a really old way"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 653658.0,
      "end_time": 655725.0,
      "text": "of seeing the seas:"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 655749.0,
      "end_time": 659279.0,
      "text": "as delicate, precious places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 659303.0,
      "end_time": 661720.0,
      "text": "worthy of our protection."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 661896.0,
      "end_time": 663651.0,
      "text": "Our oceans are sacred."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 663675.0,
      "end_time": 665175.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 665200.0,
      "end_time": 668134.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}